2
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:18,510
March24,1947

3
00:00:18,850 --> 00:00:21,450
All right,open up,son.
I can't do it by myself.

4
00:00:22,460 --> 00:00:24,090
Come on,no half-steppin',ladies.

5
00:00:27,020 --> 00:00:28,240
push it up.

6
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:34,090
six feet,girls.

7
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:37,730
First shift burrowed under the river five feet.
That means that we go six.

8
00:00:39,090 --> 00:00:40,990
That's a nice shiny new helmet there,nate.

9
00:00:40,990 --> 00:00:42,840
Couldn't get one with a little flashlight?

10
00:00:44,040 --> 00:00:46,650
Wife wouldn't let me back down
in the hole without a hard hat.

11
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:50,800
At least your old lady cares
if you get cracked in the dome.

12
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,620
Oh,my sister treating you that bad these days?

13
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:55,230
What do you mean "these days"?

14
00:00:55,230 --> 00:00:58,590
Tell you what alice cooked up last night,
but I don't want to rub it in.

15
00:00:58,940 --> 00:01:00,390
You're lucky you got a woman like that.

16
00:01:00,390 --> 00:01:02,990
Woman who don't give a man no quarter,you mean.

17
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:11,230
cave-in or blowout don't get your father-in-law,
that cough will.

18
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:14,850
He ought to retire.
Let someone carry the weight of foreman.

19
00:01:14,850 --> 00:01:17,040
- That'll be you,donny.
- You think?

20
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:20,810
Like I said,my wife's counting on you
to bring all of us up out of here.

21
00:01:20,810 --> 00:01:22,570
All them stories you tell...

22
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:24,930
it'd be nice to finally meet old alice.

23
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,920
Not in this here world.

24
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:30,860
Down here every joe's blood runs brown--
same as the muck.

25
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:32,740
But not up there.

26
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:37,480
I'm fine.
I'm fine.

27
00:01:39,130 --> 00:01:41,350
- Get back to work.
- Hey,nate!

28
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,890
Watch it there,nate.

29
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:55,460
Eight million ways to die every day.

30
00:01:55,730 --> 00:01:57,120
Not today.

31
00:01:57,940 --> 00:01:59,590
Not today.

32
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:51,970
Figure on stretching that shirt out another day?

33
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:55,960
You want to check my shorts there too,hoss?

34
00:02:57,430 --> 00:03:00,030
Transit workers found the body expanding the subway.

35
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:02,080
Five stories under the river.

36
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,640
I ain't going down there.

37
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,800
What's the matter,don't like tunnels?

38
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,060
They got rats the size of badgers.

39
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:11,220
No,man,even the rats hate it down there.

40
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:14,730
Bulldozer broke through an old service tunnel.
Found the bones.

41
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:17,740
Still Adult male.
Blunt force trauma to the skull.

42
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:21,260
Found behind a tunnel that got sealed in 1948.

43
00:03:21,260 --> 00:03:23,580
Guy needs a paleontologist,not a detective.

44
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:25,720
Could be one of those mole people?

45
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:28,430
Wasn't a mole,this was a sandhog.

46
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:30,680
- Sandhog?
- Urban miner.

47
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,660
Died with his boots on.

48
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:36,150
S "compressed air worker,number 505.
"If found sick or unconscious,

49
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:40,450
"return to medical decompression lock
at bertleman construction site."

50
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:44,740
Sandhogs were required to carry those badges at all times,
in case of an attack of the bends.

51
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,290
How's a miner get the bends?

52
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:48,460
Working deep underground in compressed air.

53
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:50,860
Tunnels,subways,sewers...
you name it.

54
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:53,350
Say if it's deeper than a grave,a sandhog dug it.

55
00:03:53,350 --> 00:03:55,350
Looks like this poor schmuck might have dug his own.

56
00:03:55,350 --> 00:03:59,550
You see those miners trapped on the news,
they move heaven and earth to get a guy out.

57
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:01,790
At least,recover a body.

58
00:04:02,730 --> 00:04:04,930
This guy didn't get left behind.

59
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,780
He got buried on purpose.

